SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c04530570
Version: 1

HPSBOV03225 rev.1 - HP OpenVMS running POP, Remote Denial of Service (DoS)

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2014-12-16
Last Updated: 2014-12-16

- -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
- --

Potential Security Impact: Remote Denial of Service (DoS)

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
Potential security vulnerabilities have been identified with HP OpenVMS POP.
The vulnerabilities could be exploited remotely to create a server Denial of
Service (DoS).

References:

CVE-2014-7880 (SSRT101328)

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP OpenVMS TCPIP V5.7 prior to ECO5

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2014-7880    (AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:N/I:N/A:C)       7.8
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

RESOLUTION

HP has made the following software update available to resolve the
vulnerabilities with HP OpenVMS Integrity Servers running POP.

HP OpenVMS TCPIP V5.7 ECO5 package is available from the following location:

The HP OpenVMS TCP/IP V5.7 ECO5 kits for both Integrity and Alpha platforms
have been uploaded to HP Support Center website. Customers can access the
kits from Patch Management page.

https://h20566.www2.hp.com/portal/site/hpsc/patch/home/

Patch ID of kit for Alpha platform: DEC-AXPVMS-TCPIP-V0507-13ECO5-1

Patch Bundle / ID
 Description

DEC-AXPVMS-TCPIP-V0507-13ECO5-1
 TCPIP V5.7 ECO5

Patch ID of kit for Integrity platform: HP-I64VMS-TCPIP-V0507-13ECO5-1

Patch Bundle / ID
 Description

HP-I64VMS-TCPIP-V0507-13ECO5-1
 TCP/IP V5.7 ECO5

